<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    <a href="?t=95837887800003&r=1&w=2">bogus information from nameservers</a>
From:       <a href="?a=95837693600004&r=1&w=2">bloom () monet ! berkeley ! edu (Jim Bloom)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198510">1985-10-31 14:43:31</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426589&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837667426589&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I found that several domains are initializing their caches with incorrect
nameservers for the root domain.  They all are using usc-isif.arpa as a
root domain server which is incorrect.  The current root domain servers
are usc-isib.arpa, usc-isic.arpa, sri-nic.arpa, and brl-aos.arpa.

Specifically, the following domains have incorrect databases:

	columbia.edu
	rice.edu
	utexas.edu
	cmu.edu
	umd.edu
	cornell.edu
	mit.edu

I haven't done an exhaustive test, just the nameservers that we talked to
within a 15 minute period.  My tests covered less than twenty domains.  I
also found one site propogating information that it had received which
would be much harder to avoid.

					Jim Bloom

